name: sweet potato fries
notes: |
  Fallow's method (https://www.youtube.com/shorts/7URIUFUgtxw).
  Sweet potatoes have more sugar & water and less starch than regular potatoes,
  so the surface caramelises and burns before the fry crisps. The fix is a thick,
  layered coating plus a low fry temperature so the crust sets before the sugars catch.
components:
  - name: coating
    ingredients:
      - item: plain flour
        note: body
      - item: corn flour
        note: light crispiness
      - item: rice flour
        note: locks in moisture, keeps fries crispy
      - item: bicarbonate of soda
        note: lift
      - item: baking powder
        note: lift
    steps:
      - mix the flours, bicarb and baking powder well
  - name: liquid
    ingredients:
      - water
      - item: white wine vinegar
        note: lowers surface pH to slow caramelisation as it cooks
steps:
  - peel and cut sweet potatoes into 1cm batons
  - dust the sweet potatoes with a third of the flour mix
  - pour over half the liquid
  - repeat until all the flour mix and liquid is worked through (flour should be last step, builds a thick, structured coating the potato can't form on its own)
  - heat oil to 160°C (lower than you'd expect) and fry for 4 mins so the coating sets before the sugars catch
  - onto a wire rack and season immediately
